This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with video analysis and action recognition. The use of audio analysis also suggests it could belong to the signal processing (cs.SD) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of contrastive loss, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and the use of self-supervised learning, which could also place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of negative examples, which suggests it could also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
